  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison had tea with Mr. (William?) Green. Garrison writes: &quot;In the forenoon I went with Mr. McKim, Lucy, and Mr. Haydock to a small hall in Orange, where a meeting was held with reference to Lucretia Mott. About a hundred persons were present.&quot; He gives an account of Mrs. Oliver Johnson&apos;s funeral. Garrison stayed with Mr. and Mrs. Haydock afterward.</subfield>
